    {
      "id": "8a90cf5e_3157335a",
      "file_path": "src/test/java/org/onap/dcae/common/validator/GeneralEventValidatorTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 97,
      "message": "I would propose something like below instead of these all try-catches with fail(). It eliminates false-positive mistakes in tests and it's more readable. Probably may be better formatted so treat it more like a hint.\n------------------------------------------------------\n\nExecutable testedMethod = () -> sut.validate(new VesEvent(jsonObject), \"wrongType\", DUMMY_SCHEMA_VERSION);\n\nEventValidatorException thrownException = assertThrows(EventValidatorException.class, testedMethod);\nassertEquals(ApiException.SCHEMA_VALIDATION_FAILED, thrownException.getApiException());",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5234,
        "name": "Micha? Ba?ka",
        "display_name": "Michal Banka",
        "email": "michal.banka@nokia.com",
        "username": "michal.banka"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-23 14:59:30.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "baf78db1_c32c3dc2",
      "file_path": "src/test/java/org/onap/dcae/common/validator/GeneralEventValidatorTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 135,
      "message": "And instead of try-catches without fail(), just use:\n\nassertDoesNotThrow(() -> sut.validate(new VesEvent(jsonObject), DUMMY_TYPE, DUMMY_SCHEMA_VERSION));",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5234,
        "name": "Micha? Ba?ka",
        "display_name": "Michal Banka",
        "email": "michal.banka@nokia.com",
        "username": "michal.banka"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-23 14:59:30.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
